**Best Solution to the following assignment problem given to the undergraduate 
students of ECE department for the fullfillment of the course on "Optical Communications"**

## Problem Definition
SMF PROBLEM:
GIVEN
Three products for SMF (single mode fiber) transmission at a wavelength;
* 1.3 micro-meter= 1300nm
* 1.5 micro-meter= 1500nm
* Both 1.3 and 1.5 micro-meter
Create design curve that co-relate the core diameter, d to the fractional index change, delta.
Consider the silica fiber core (n=1.46) and then
a) Design for a step-index profile
b) Design for a quadratic graded profile (p=2)
c) Finally show the variation of NA (numerical aperture) with the acceptance angle with your choices

    "### First CASE :\n",
    "Transmission at 1.3 μm\n",
    "\n",
    "Core refractive index, n =1.46\n",
    "\n",
    "λo = 1.3 μm =1300 nm.\n",
    "\n",
    "### From cheat sheet:\n",
    "\n",
    "V = 2 Π(a/λo)*(NA)\n",
    "\n",
    "& NA = n* √(2Δ)\n",
    "\n",
    "D = 2a\n",
    "\n",
    "V = Πd/λo*n* √(2Δ)\n",
    "\n",
    "### A) SI profile\n",
    "\n",
    "For SI SMF, V <=2.405\n",
    "\n",
    "Therefore, \n",
    "\n",
    "2.405 = Πd* √(2Δ)*1.46 / 1300*10e-9\n",
    "\n",
    "By solving we get: (1/d2) = 4.30 * 10^12* Δ\n",
    "\n",
    "### B) GI profile\n",
    "\n",
    "M = V2/4\n",
    "\n",
    "For SMF, \n",
    "\n",
    "M = 1\n",
    "V = 2\n",
    "\n",
    "V = Πd/λo*n* √(2Δ)\n",
    "\n",
    "Solving the above eq. \n",
    "We get, \n",
    "\n",
    "(1/d2) = 6.22 * 10^12* Δ"
   ]

    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt \n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import math\n",
    "\n",
    "# for step\n",
    "# x axis values in power 10^12 and round-off\n",
    "delta_step = [round(num, 3) for num in np.linspace(0.001, 0.020, 10)]\n",
    "delta = delta_step\n",
    "\n",
    "# corresponding y axis values and round-off\n",
    "d_square_step = [round(num, 3) for num in [math.sqrt(1/(x*4.3)) for x in delta]]\n",
    "\n",
    "# for graded\n",
    "delta_graded = delta_step\n",
    "\n",
    "# corresponding y axis values and round-off\n",
    "d_square_graded= [round(num, 3) for num in [math.sqrt(1/(x*6.22)) for x in delta]]\n",
    "\n",
    "# plotting the points  \n",
    "plt.plot(delta_step, d_square_step, color='green', linewidth = 1, \n",
    "         marker='o', markerfacecolor='green', markersize=5) \n",
    "plt.plot(delta_graded, d_square_graded, color='blue', linewidth = 1, \n",
    "         marker='o', markerfacecolor='blue', markersize=5) \n",
    "\n",
    "# naming the x axis \n",
    "plt.ylabel('diameter(micrometer)') \n",
    "# naming the y axis \n",
    "plt.xlabel('delta') \n",
    "plt.legend([\"step (1300 um)\", \"graded (1300 um)\"], loc =\"upper right\") \n",
    "\n",
    "# giving a title to my graph \n",
    "plt.title('diameter vs delta for transmission at 1.3 micrometer') \n",
    "# function to show the plot \n",
    "plt.show() \n",
    "plt\n",
    "\n",

    "results in a diameter value ranging from 3 to 12 um for step-index profile\n",

    "and \n",

    "\n",
    "Dividing the range of delta can be broadened to achieve a more accurate\n",

    "\n",
    "### For NA vs acceptance angle, \n",

    "\n",
    "θa = sin-1(NA)\n",
    "\n",
    "Now Plot NA vs θa\n",
    "\n",
    "As we increase the value of delta, the light gathering capability, \n",
    "NA and the acceptance angle of the fiber also increases, \n",
    "but for SMF smaller values of NA is preferred because of less \n",
    "losses and can be used for long\n",
    "distance communication."

    "## Third Case:\n",
    "\n",
    "### Transmission at both 1.3 and 1.5 μm\n",
    "\n",
    "Core refractive index, n =1.46\n",
    "λmin = 8 μm\n",
    "λmax = 10 μm\n",
    "\n",
    "### A) SI profile\n",
    "\n",
    "For SI SMF, V <=2.405\n",
    "\n",
    "For 1300 μm (1/d2) = 4.30 * 1012* Δ\n",
    "\n",
    "Put dmin = 8 and dmax = 10 to get corresponding values of Δ\n",
    "\n",
    "For 1500 μm (1/d2) = 3.23 * 1012* Δ\n",
    "\n",
    "Put dmin = 8 and dmax = 10 to get corresponding values of Δ\n",
    "\n",
    "### B) GI profile\n",
    "\n",
    "M = V2/4\n",
    "\n",
    "For SMF, M = 1\n",
    "\n",
    "V = 2\n",
    "\n",
    "V = Πd/λo*n* √(2Δ)\n",
    "\n",
    "Solving the above eq. We get, (1/d2) = 4.67 * 1012* Δ\n",
    "\n",
    "When we set the optimum range of core diameter we want, we can according vary the refractive index contrast\n",
    "value from 0.001 to 0.005 for optimum performance at 1300 and 1500 nm. Lowest delta values are observed for\n",
    "1300 nm transmission wavelength graded index fiber.\n",
    "\n",
    "We can observe that as we increase the delta values, our NA and Acceptance angle values in degrees also\n",
    "increases. The step-index single mode fiber at 1500 nm with core diameter of 8 um has the highest value of\n",
    "delta as observed from the calculations whereas the Graded Index SMF at 1300nm at 10um has lowest delta.\n",
    "According to the desired area of application, the value of diameter can be chosen weighing the advantages of a\n",
    "lower or higher value of NA. Since SMF is required, a lower delta will be preferable as losses are less and\n",
    "coupling efficiency is also high."
